<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Playboy-Lorimar,0113</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Playboy, Lorimar Settle Home Video Dispute</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lorimar Home Video will pay Playboy Video at
least $1 million to settle a contract dispute over distribution of
Playboy's home video products, Playboy Enterprises Inc. said Friday.
   The settlement ends arbitration proceedings begun last fall over
Playboy's claims that Los Angeles-based Lorimar had breached a
two-year contract to distribute Playboy video materials. The
contract had been set to run through this month.
   Playboy did not specify the amount of the settlement, but
Playboy Video President Richard V. Sowa called it a ``seven-figure
sum.''
   Playboy, based in Chicago, recently signed a new video
distribution agreement with HBO Video.
</TEXT>
