<1ST_LINE>r a AM-MurderArrests     04-16 0219</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Murder Arrests,0226</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two More Arrested In Connection With Maryland Murders</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The FBI arrested two men Friday in the
drug-related slayings of five people in a Maryland apartment Jan.
22.
   Steven McMillian, 24, and Kirk Bruce, 25, were arrested in a
raid on an apartment in the Bronx by the FBI and police, said FBI
spokesman Gary Perkins.
   The two were arrested on a federal charge of unlawful flight to
avoid prosecution, based on a murder warrant in Maryland, Perkins
said.
   An FBI source speaking on condition of anonymity said agents
confiscated a .45-caliber weapon believed to have been used in the
slayings of four men and a woman in Landover, Md.
   Police said the victims had been involved in drug trafficking
organizations since the early 1980s and were shot in the head and
chest with semi-automatic weapons.
   On Saturday, police arrested Carl Dunstrom, 28, in Brooklyn in
the slayings.
   The slayings were featured in a March 13 episode of ``America's
Most Wanted,'' a half-hour series on Fox Television in which
viewers are shown photographs and given information on fugitives
and asked to provide tips.
   Authorities in Prince George's County, Md., said last week the
show generated nearly 100 tips, but Perkins said he did not know
whether the program led to Friday's raid.
