<HEAD>Venus and the Moon To Nestle In The Sky</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Skywatchers will have a chance to see Venus
nestled near the emerging Moon, with the peak viewing time to come
just after twilight on Tuesday night.
   The celestial couple also will shine together on Sunday and
Monday nights, according to Sky & Telescope magazine.
   ``It'll be a particularly nice scene, and folks will notice
it,'' said Gail Cleere of the U.S. Naval Observatory here.
   The Moon will be just three days old on Tuesday, so it will be a
pretty crescent, Cleere said. ``We gets hundreds of calls'' when
instances like this occur.
