<HEAD>President Plans Visit To China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBLIN, Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Patrick Hillery will visit
China in May, becoming the first Irish head of state to visit the
communist nation, the government announced.
   During his one-week state visit, Hillery is to visit the
hometown of the philosopher Confucius, the government said Friday.
   Hillery will arrive May 8 and will be the guest of honor the
next day at a banquet given by President Yang Shungkun at the Great
