<HEAD>9 Students Crushed to Death When School Building Collapses</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A mud wall collapsed in a junior high school
dormitory, crushing nine students to death and wounding four
others, a official newspaper reported today.
   The state-run People's Daily said the boys' dormitory of the
Mianjin Junior High School in Jiangxi province collapsed Monday
night after heavy rainfall.
   The building, built in 1940, was poorly maintained, needed
repair and was considered dangerous for occupation, the paper said.
   The People's Daily said it was the second school building
collapse in the province in 16 months. An elementary school
building collapsed in January 1987, killing 28 students.
   Provincial authorities called for greater attention to the
maintenance of school buildings after the first incident, but the
paper said local authorities ignored the problem.
