<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--BogusMovie     04-16 0171</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Bogus Movie,0175</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Attorney General Shuts Down Casting Agency Scam</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SALEM, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A company that charged would-be movie stars
$25 to be interviewed for a role in a horror movie is a phony and
should be closed down, the state attorney general's office said.
   Rocky Mountain Central Casting Co. is believed to have run
similar operations in eight other states, said Jan Margosian, a
spokeswoman for the state Department of Justice, which filed a
lawsuit Friday.
   She said the company told prospective clients it was
interviewing people _ for a fee of $25 _ for a role in a horror
movie called ``The Closet'' to be produced by Osmond Studios in
Orem, Utah.
   However, no such movie was planned, according to Jimmie Osmond,
a spokesman for the studios.
   The lawsuit, filed in Marion County Circuit Court, named as
defendants Royal, Joyce and Chris Christenson, operators of Rocky
Mountain Central Casting.
   The lawsuit said the company is a Wyoming corporation but is not
registered to do business in Oregon.
</TEXT>
