<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Wine Directory,0152</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>New U.S. Wine Lists Show Record Wineries In Nation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The newly released 1988 directory of the
Wineries of North America lists a record 1,240 wineries in the
United States, including 105 new producers.
   Of the new wineries, 46 are in California, 12 each are in New
York State and Oregon; Washington State, 10; Idaho and Tennessee,
five each; Virginia, four; New Mexico, three, and Texas, two, and
one each in Connecticut, Indiana, Kentucky, Missouri, Ohio and
Vermont.
   Published by the authoritative trade journal Wines & Vines, the
directory lists 648 wineries in California, where 90 percent of all
American wines, 95 percent of all table grapes and nearly all the
brandy is produced.
   The leading wine-producing states after California are New York,
91; Oregon, 64; Washington State, 63; Pennsylvania, 41; Ohio, 39;
Virginia, 34; Missouri, 29; New Mexico, 20, and Texas, 20.
