<HEAD>Man Charged With Killing Elderly Woman Who Put Him In Jail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who had been imprisoned for
stealing money from his former employer has been accused of
returning to the elderly woman's house and killing her, two weeks
after his release.
   Isaac Fields, 31, was charged Friday with murder, kidnapping and
burglary, said Maj. Larry Campbell of the Leon County Sheriff's
office. Other charges were pending.
   The body of 79-year-old Jane May Dougherty, who suffered from
rheumatoid arthritis and was unable to walk without a cane, was
found inside a storage room in her home.
   Campbell said she was struck on the head Tuesday with a blunt
instrument, but investigators did not find the body until Thursday,
even though they had been looking for her since she disappeared.
   Sheriff's spokesman Dick Simpson also said initial evidence
indicated she had been kidnapped.
   Ms. Dougherty had hired Fields to help with her gardening,
neighbors said.
   Last May, Fields was charged with stealing money and checks from
her. Campbell said he went into her house and rifled through her
purse.
   He was convicted of forgery, burglary and grand theft on Oct. 6
and was sentenced to three years in prison. However, he was
released March 31.
   Campbell declined to speculate if revenge was a factor in the
slaying.
