<HEAD>Vail Couple Takes 180 Holiday Inns in 20 States to the Cleaners</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VAIL, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A federal grand jury has indicted a couple on
charges of taking more than 180 Holiday Inns in 20 states to the
cleaners for more than $6,000.
   Keith W. Froemming and Joan M. Atwell were indicted on seven
counts of conspiracy, mail fraud and bank fraud.
   The indictment alleged that Froemming wrote managers of each
hotel that coffee had been spilled on his wife's suede skirt when
the couple visited the hotel's restaurant during a business trip.
   Froemming claimed the staff told him to send the cleaning bill,
and he enclosed a bill for $30.16, the indictment said.
   The ploy, begun around March 1, apparently worked, the
indictment said. About 200 checks totaling more than $6,000 were
sent to a private post office box in Vail in March, authorities
said.
