<1ST_LINE>u i AM-Venezuela-Shootings     04-16 0251</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Venezuela-Shootings,0260</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Venezuelan Marine Killed In Attack By Colombians</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Venezuelan marine sergeant was
killed and two other soldiers were wounded when Colombian
guerrillas fired on their barge on on the Arauca River, the Defense
Ministry said Saturday.
   Colombians fired on another Venezuelan vessel in the same area
two hours later but there were no casualties, the ministry said in
a statement.
   The death is the first this year of a Venezuelan soldier in a
border clash with Colombians.
   The fatal attack occurred when the dredging barge was clearing a
section of the river about 360 miles southwest of Caracas. The
river forms part of the border between the two countries.
   ``A group of presumed Colombian common criminals in a canoe .. .
opened fire suddenly upon the dredge, mortally wounding Sgt. Luis
Malave Cordoba and inflicting minor wounds on two other marine
infantrymen,'' the ministry said.
   The ministry did not say if the Venezuelans returned fire or if
there were Colombian casualties.
   Gen. Humberto Camejo Arias said military reinforcements have
been sent to the area to search for ``foreign subversives and
probable accomplices.''
   Venezuela increased its military presence on the border in
January because of an increase in kidnappings of Venezuelans by
Colombians and the use of Venezuelan territory by Colombian cocaine
gangs.
   In January, Venezuelan soldiers killed five Colombians in an
exchange of fire across the Arauca River.
   The two nations agreed to coordinate efforts to cut down on
border activity by Colombian criminals.
</TEXT>
