<HEAD>Police Capture Kidnapping Suspect, Recover $1 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police captured a suspect Friday
in the abduction of a wealthy businessman's two sons and recovered
more than $1 million in a ransom payment during a shootout,
television reported.
   TV Globo said one of the suspected kidnappers fled during the
shootout in the southern resort town of Balneario Camboriu, 570
miles southwest of Rio.
   The family paid the ransom on Monday and the two sons of Saul
Brandalise Jr., Saul 14 and Jean Paul 8, were freed Wednesday.
   According to the television network, which showed tape of the
gunfight, police tracked two suspects to a hotel in the resort town.
   It said police and the alleged kidnappers exchanged shots for
several hours and one of the suspects was wounded and surrendered
while the other fled.
   Police recovered more than $1 million of the $1.2 million ransom
paid by the family, the report said.
   The boys were kidnapped April 7 from the family home in Videira,
a rural town 900 miles southwest of Rio. Their father is the
president of the Perdiagao Food Processing Group.
</TEXT>
