<2ND_LINE>BC-Tandy, CORRECTIVE,0126</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>Eds: Members that used BC-Tandy, transmitted April 5 in advance
for weekend editions of April 9-10, are asked to use the following
story.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press erroneously
reported April 9 that Tandy Corp. had begun a major push to
increase sales to large companies last year by creating separate
computer centers and spending $80 million to refurbish outlets.
   Tandy began opening separate computer centers in 1978 and did
the $80 million in renovations on outlets other than the computer
centers. The company has 4,900 outlets instead of 8,500 as stated.
In addition, Tandy said it does not intend to sell computers made
by the recently acquired Grid Systems Corp. through Radio Shack
marketing channels.
</TEXT>
